 deaths, bringing the death toll to 22,170. Italian authorities have also reported 3,76 cases, bringing the total to 168,941. 2,936 remain in intensive care while 40,164 have recovered.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 16 April reports\" />\n*Japan has reported a total of about 9,000 cases (including three cabinet officials) and nearly 200 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 17 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia reports 110 new cases, bringing the total number of cases to 5,182. Malaysian authorities report one death, bringing the total to 84. 2,766 patients have recovered while 2,332 are still being treated.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kaos |first1=Joseph, Jr. |title=Covid-19: 110 new cases, death toll now at 84 |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/16/covid-19-110-new-cases-death-toll-now-at-84 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=16 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200416102916/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/16/covid-19-110-new-cases-death-toll-now-at-84 |archivedate=16 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Malaysia reports 110 new coronavirus cases with one new death |url=https://www.thesundaily.my/local/malaysia-reports-110-new-coronavirus-cases-with-one-new-death-BY2265982 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |work=[[The Sun (Malaysia)|The Sun Daily]] |date=16 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200416103313/https://www.thesundaily.my/local/malaysia-reports-110-new-coronavirus-cases-with-one-new-death-BY2265982 |archivedate=16 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*The Netherlands reports 1,061 new cases, bringing the total to 29,214. Dutch authorities report 181 deaths, bringing the death toll to 3,315.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 16 April reports\" />\n*New Zealand reports 15 new cases (six confirmed and nine probable), bringing the total to 1,401. 12 people remain in hospital with three in intensive care and two in critical condition. 42 people have recovered, bringing the total 