 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 5,957. Iran has reported a total of 93,657 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia has reported 94 new cases, bringing the total to 5,945. 55 patients were discharged, bringing the number of recoveries to 4,087. The country's death toll remains at 100.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kaos Jr |first1=Joseph |title=Covid-19 update: 94 new cases reported, no new deaths |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/29/covid-19-update-94-new-cases-reported-no-new-deaths |accessdate=29 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=29 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200429095458/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/29/covid-19-update-94-new-cases-reported-no-new-deaths |archivedate=29 April 2020}}</ref>\n*New Zealand has reported two new cases (one confirmed and two probables), bringing the total to 1,474 (1,126 confirmed and 348 probable). NZ health authorities also reported 15 new recoveries were reported, bringing the total to 1,229.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|publisher=New Zealand Government|date=29 April 2020|access-date=29 April 2020|archive-date=29 April 2020|archive-url=}}</ref>\n*Pakistan has reported 26 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 327. Pakistan has also reported 806 new cases, bringing the total to 14,885. A total of at least 3,245 patients have recovered.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*Poland has reported a total of 12,415 cases and 606 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*Russia has reported 5,841 new cases, bringing the total number to 99,399. Russia's has reported 108 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 972.\n*Singapore has reported 690 new cases, bringing the total to 15,641.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Iau |first1=Jean |title=690 new coronavirus cases take Singapore tally past 15,000 mark |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/690-new-coronavirus-cases-take-singapore-tally-past-15000-mark |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=29 April 2020 |date=29 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Spain has reported 325 deaths, bringing the death toll to 24,275. Spain has reported 2,144 cases, bringing the total to 212,917.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*Turkey has reported a total of nearly 115,000 cases and nearly 3,000 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n<!--\n===30 April===\n-->\n\n== Summary ==\n\n===Timeline===\n\nCountries and territories that confirmed their first cases during April 2020:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5em;\"  | Date\n! style=\"width:25em;\" | Country or territory\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2 April\n| {{flagdeco|Malawi}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malawi|Malawi]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3 April\n| {{flagdeco|Falkland Islands}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Falkland Islands|Falkland Islands]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4 April\n| [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Western Sahara|Western Sahara]]{{efn|In the Moroccan-controlled part.}}\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5 April\n| {{flagdeco|Saint Pierre and Miquelon|local}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Pierre and Miquelon|Saint Pierre and Miquelon]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|South Sudan}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Sudan|South Sudan]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6 April\n| {{flagdeco|S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe|S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe]]\n|- style=\"background:#fff;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7 April\n| {{flagdeco|Abkhazia}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Abkhazia|Abkhazia]] \u2022 {{flagdeco|Artsakh}}