e reports 401 new cases and 19 new deaths, bringing the total numbers to 9,410 and 239 respectively; a total of 992 patients have recovered.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e 9410 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0445\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438 COVID-19 |url=https://www.facebook.com/moz.ukr/posts/1521379661358467 |website=facebook.com |publisher=Ministry of Healthcare of Ukraine |accessdate=28 April 2020 |language=uk |date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The United States has reported over 1 million cases and more than 57,000 deaths as a result of the coronavirus pandemic. Illinois has reported 142 deaths, bringing the total to 2,125. Illinois has also reported 2,219 cases, bringing the total to 48,102.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 28 April reports\" />\n\n===29 April===\n*Azerbaijan has reported a total of nearly 1,717 cases and 22 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\">{{cite news |last1=Mayberry |first1=Kate |last2=Aziz |first2=Saba |title=Coronavirus cases exceed 3 million, a third in US: Live updates |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/coronavirus-cases-exceed-3-million-live-updates-200428233945104.html |accessdate=29 April 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=29 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Brazil has reported 474 deaths, bringing the death toll to 5,017.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*China has reported 22 new cases, all involving overseas travel. Chinese authorities reported no new deaths, with the official death toll remaining 4,633.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*Germany has reported 1,304 new cases and 202 more deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*India has reported 73 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 1,007. India has reported over 30,000 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 29 April reports\" />\n*Indonesia